is a Japanese light novel series written by Ryō Ariyama and illustrated by Kodama (first volume) and Ryō Kamito (from second volume). It began serialization online in August 2019 on the user-generated novel publishing website Shōsetsuka ni Narō. It was later acquired by Shogakukan, who have published five volumes and a side story volume since June 2020 under their Gagaga Books imprint. A manga adaptation with art by Kamito has been serialized via the Manga Doa app since April 2021 and has been collected in five  volumes by Mag Garden. An anime television series adaptation is set to premiere in 2026.
Media
Light novel
Written by Ryō Ariyama, ''Romelia War Chronicle: The Count's Daughter Rallies an Army in the Wake of Mankind's Victory began serialization on the user-generated web novel publishing site Shōsetsuka ni Narō on August 26, 2019. It was later acquired by Shogakukan who began publishing it as a light novel with illustrations by Kodama and Ryō Kamito under their Gagaga Books light novel imprint on June 19, 2020. Five volumes and a side story volume have been released as of September 2024. The series will end with the release of its sixth volume.
